              href="https://github.com/Simodalstix/terraform-postgres-rds-migration"
              target="_blank"
              class="mt-auto self-end text-cyan-400 hover:underline text-xs"
            >
              View on GitHub
            </a>
          </div>

          <!-- RIGHT COLUMN: Description + bullets -->
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <h3 class="text-white text-base text-center font-semibold">
                Database Migration PostgresSQL to Amazon RDS
              </h3>
              <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-300">
                <p>
                  This project focused on a realistic migration scenario: taking a local PostgreSQL
                  database and moving it to the cloud using AWS RDS. I designed the architecture
                  with Terraform, including a VPC with public and private subnets, a Bastion host
                  accessed via SSM Session Manager, and Secrets Manager for secure credential
                  handling — avoiding any exposed ports or direct SSH.
                </p>
                <p>
                  The database was staged through S3 and restored using psql, closely mimicking how
                  a secure cloud transition might be handled in production. It gave me practical
                  insight into infrastructure planning, data transfer, and how to combine security
                  best practices with infrastructure-as-code.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Project 3 -->
      <div class="p-4 border border-gray-600 rounded bg-gray-700 text-gray-200">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-4 h-full">
          <!-- LEFT COLUMN: 2-wide icon grid -->
